profile_positions.description:
As part of KNCV's Digital Health Solutions team, I am working to:

• Serve as a digital health visionary and contribute to KNCV’s Digital Health strategy;
• Lead and provide technical assistance to National Tuberculosis Programs (NTP) in the design and deployment of digital solutions, including medication adherence technologies, case management platforms, and diagnostic connectivity;
• Work with international partners, such as country offices, technology companies, NTPs, ministries of health, NGO’s and the WHO, to build in country capacity related to the use of digital health for tuberculosis;
• Support development of a standardized approach for the implementation of digital health tools in order to catalyze the uptake in focus countries;
• Evaluate information systems, tools, strategies and best practices from the international health community and beyond in support of determining KNCV programmatic use of digital health tools;
• Provide technical assistance to focus countries on how they collect, analyze and use data to improve the efficiency and effectiveness of their efforts to fight tuberculosis;
• Support country-led efforts in Kyrgyzstan, Ukraine, Nigeria, Philippines, Ethiopia, Indonesia, Tanzania, and India to leverage the use of innovative technologies for improved health outcomes.
